this folder is the directory to place generated TeX
files for transcribed ink notes used the indexed DAG
format I've been developing.

to get this working, there are a lot of small steps involved,
so below will be an unordered and possibly incomplete
list of items needed to get these rendered.

first, figures need to be rendered in EPS format. These
are rendered by the script in dz/ink/transcriptions/generate.sh.
It should create a folder called dz/ink/figs containing
the output. figs should be linked to this ink folder.

to render figures, DAGDraw needs to be built. Run the build
script located in tools/dagdraw.

If the ink transcriptions are regenerated, the knowledge
graph might need to be regenerated. 'mkdz' should be fine instead
of the slower 'gendb' script. logs aren't required to be regenerated.

To add another note to generate, append entries to the 'note.txt'
file. The first column is the output name (no extension), and
the second column is the namespace pattern to search for.
